      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/ecd19e/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2023-10-12T08:03:06.212Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hello after summer <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/alex\">@Alex</a></p>\n<p>Recently I\u2019ve started to use my home trainer again and straight away I\u2019ve encountered similar and other issues. Let me explain:<br>\n<a href=\"https://app.trainerday.com/activities/651fa47a6d551bc8fcbef015\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://app.trainerday.com/activities/651fa47a6d551bc8fcbef015</a><br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1ffefd2b75b0f26ce2f4074378a8d5643e4ebb9c.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/1ffefd2b75b0f26ce2f4074378a8d5643e4ebb9c\" title=\"6oct\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1ffefd2b75b0f26ce2f4074378a8d5643e4ebb9c_2_690x305.png\" alt=\"6oct\" data-base62-sha1=\"4z36ZTV8ROA3RjVnRJgJxmqccBS\" width=\"690\" height=\"305\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1ffefd2b75b0f26ce2f4074378a8d5643e4ebb9c_2_690x305.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1ffefd2b75b0f26ce2f4074378a8d5643e4ebb9c_2_1035x457.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1ffefd2b75b0f26ce2f4074378a8d5643e4ebb9c.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1ffefd2b75b0f26ce2f4074378a8d5643e4ebb9c_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">6oct</span><span class=\"informations\">1152\u00d7510 82.5 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Random power curve change. Seems to be in line with the curve but offseted. Pause + restart recovery.</li>\n<li>Random change of curve. It looks like trainer is constantly increasing resistance. Pause + restart recovery.</li>\n<li>The same as number two.</li>\n<li>Change of gearing on rear cassette to higher sprocket. You can see instantaneous reduction of power and counter reaction from trainer, however last home season I\u2019ve changed gears sometimes and trainer has stabilized this fluctuation of power after no more than 5 seconds and after that average power was on par with requested by workout. Now it looks like power has been stabilized on much higher level. Pause + restart recovery.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://app.trainerday.com/activities/652392316d551bc8fcda6b40\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://app.trainerday.com/activities/652392316d551bc8fcda6b40</a></p>\n<p>HR mode. Both peaks are just random offset applied to requested power. Pause + restart recovery.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://app.trainerday.com/activities/652784d5dc5b1d887866680b\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://app.trainerday.com/activities/652784d5dc5b1d887866680b</a><br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1f62fce323b651adf7617f6688de63636c1c75c7.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/1f62fce323b651adf7617f6688de63636c1c75c7\" title=\"12oct\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1f62fce323b651adf7617f6688de63636c1c75c7_2_690x306.png\" alt=\"12oct\" data-base62-sha1=\"4tESGCnouC0OASwKFUBuaS79wi3\" width=\"690\" height=\"306\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1f62fce323b651adf7617f6688de63636c1c75c7_2_690x306.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1f62fce323b651adf7617f6688de63636c1c75c7_2_1035x459.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1f62fce323b651adf7617f6688de63636c1c75c7.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1f62fce323b651adf7617f6688de63636c1c75c7_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">12oct</span><span class=\"informations\">1167\u00d7519 77.5 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Again, change of curvature, random increased slope steepnes. Pause + restart recovery.</li>\n<li>It looks like no. 1 however in the end it has stabilized by itself.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://app.trainerday.com/workouts/endurance-60-min-2\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Trainer Day - Workout: Endurance 60 min</a> this is workout I\u2019m using. Is it somehow incorrectly described and steps needs to be adjusted?</p>\n<p>In general it looks like after summer application stability and perfomance has been decreased.</p>",
